Summary: This document is the timetable for the IS05 FT intake of the Master of Technology in Intelligent Systems program for the AY2023/2024 Semester 2. The course will cover topics such as autonomous robots and vehicles, human-robot system engineering, and intelligent robotic systems. The course will be taught by lecturers Liu Fan, Nicholas, and Nan Zhou. The classes will take place from 9:00am to 5:00pm on weekdays between 2 Feb 2024 and 23 Feb 2024. The timetable is updated as of 22/2/2024.

The timetable outlines the schedule for a course on Real Time Audio-Visual Sensing and Sense Making, taught by Tian Jing and Gary, from January 8th to January 29th, 2024. The course will take place on weekdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm, with a break on weekends. There will also be a course on Vision Systems, taught by Tian Jing and Scott, from January 15th to January 17th, 2024. The timetable also includes a course on Spatial Reasoning from Sensor Data, taught by Tian Jing, for the MTech IS program. The timetable was last updated on February 22nd, 2024.

This timetable outlines the course schedule for the ISY5005 Graduate Certificate in Intelligent Software Agents and MTech IS program for the academic year 2023/2024. The courses will be taught by lecturers Felicitas, Sam, Scott, Chen Kuang, Fangming, and Gary. The classes will be held on weekdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm, with the first session starting on January 3, 2024 and the last session on January 26, 2024. The schedule also includes a mix of Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays, with a break on January 14, 2024. This timetable was last updated on February 22, 2024.

This page outlines the timetable for the courses in the Graduate Certificate in Practical Language Processing program for the academic year 2023/2024. The courses are taught by lecturers Aobo, Gary, and Zhenzhen and take place on various days from January 31st to February 22nd, 2024. The courses cover topics such as Conversational Uls, Text Analytics, New Media and Sentiment Mining, and Text Processing Using Machine Learning. The timetable is subject to change and was last updated on February 22nd, 2024.

The IS05 FT Student Timetable for the Academic Year 2023/2024 includes several courses with different lecturers and dates. The first course, on January 31, 2024, will be taught by Rita and will focus on alternative data for Fintech innovation. The following course, on February 5, 2024, will be taught by Dave, Mao Wen, and Vishnu and will cover advanced machine learning for financial services. Another course, taught by Christine, Tian Jing, and Vishnu, will cover explainable and responsible AI for finance on March 4, 2024. The final course, on February 20, 2024, will be taught by Scott, Brian, and Nirmal

The AY2023 / 2024 Semester 2 Exam Timetable lists the exam dates and times for various graduate certificate courses in the fields of analytics, engineering, software, and financial risk management. The exams will take place in the evening from May 13 to May 17, with some exams being held on multiple days. The timetable is subject to change and was last updated on February 22, 2024.
